      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AGNAR (1) was narrowly beaten last start when third in a small field over 1200m at Rockhampton. Will be fitter for that run and should be in the finish again. STYLISH DIAMOND (9) is close to a win after a string of minor placings, the latest when second over 1100m at this track when she was handy all the way. Nicely placed to give this a mighty shake. CAPRICORNUS (2) did very well to fill a minor placing when resuming at this circuit but raced below expectations last time over 1200m at Thangool, finishing sixth and beaten 7 lengths. Finds a tougher race but a big run will not surprise. CHECK ONE TWO (4) was out of the money when resuming from a spell last start over 1200m at Rockhampton, beaten 3.5 lengths after being in contention on the corner. Fitter this time will prove harder to beat.",
